<DOC><DOCNO> AP880625-0042 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-25-88 0314EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-BRF-Dukakis-Staff     06-25 0111</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF-Dukakis-Staff,100</SECOND><HEAD>New Press Secretary Named For Mrs. Dukakis</HEAD><DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Paul Costello, a former spokesman for Ohio Gov.Richard Celeste, has been named as press secretary to KittyDukakis, wife of probable Democratic presidential nominee MichaelDukakis.   Costello on July 5 will succeed Andrew Savitz, who was promotedto the campaign's issues and communications staff, campaign managerSusan Estrich said Friday in a statement.   Costello, 35, was Celeste's spokesman from 1981-1984. He alsoserved as assistant press secretary to Roslaynn Carter during JimmyCarter's presidency.   He will take a leave of absense from his job as director ofpublic affairs for the Chicago-based Marshall Field's departmentstore chain.</TEXT></DOC>